<TITLE> BNP plans to put secy-gen post to vote </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 15 (bdnews24.com)--A sub-committee tasked to reform the BNP's constitution has suggested direct election of the secretary-general, barring a leader from heading more than one offices in a set of 40 recommendations that leave the all-powerful chairperson untouched. The sub-committee submitted the report to chairperson Khaleda Zia at a meeting of the main opposition party's highest policymaking forum, the National Standing Committee, on Sunday night. The meeting, which started at 9:30pm with Khaleda in the chair at her political office in Gulshan, reviewed the recommendations. The meeting ended minutes after midnight without any decision. Afterwards, BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain told reporters, "The standing committee meeting discussed the proposals on the party's constitutional reforms." "We have reviewed the recommendations and will sit again," Delwar said. Members Delwar, Khandaker Mosharraf Hossain, R A Gani, Moudud Ahmed, M Shamsul Islam and Mahbubur Rahman were present. The sub-committee had finalised the suggestions at its own meeting before the crucial sitting. The main opposition party will amend the constitution in the national council set for Dec 8. Sub-committee convener Tarikul Islam, also vice-president of the party, told a media briefing late Sunday night the recommendations eye constitutional reform in line with amended Representation of the People Order, a set of electoral laws. He said 44 party leaders and workers across the country proposed amendment to the party constitution. "We have formulated report at the sub-committee meeting upon reviewing the proposal of leaders at grassroots level." Islam declined to elaborate on the issue. In reply to a query, he said an overwhelming number of adherents called for a leader not being on more than one posts from the central committees down to those at the grassroots. "We have incorporated it in our recommendation," he said On the power of party chief, he said, "Nothing new has been proposed about the power of the party chairperson. It will remain as stipulated in the party constitution." He said, "Additions and amendments have been made in keeping with BNP constitution focusing on Bangladeshi nationalism and democracy." A total of 40 amendments including new and old ones have been made in the constitution, he said The press briefing was also attended by sub-committee member and party joint-secretary Nazrul Islam Khan , Rafiqul Islam Miah and others. Earlier, BNP office secretary Rizvi Ahmed told bdnews24.com the meeting would discuss progress of developing grassroots committees and preparations for the party's national council in due in December. Restructuring at different levels of the party is also on the agenda, he said. bdnews2
